almost a month since my last post. wow has time flown...

i have been redeemed. there are absolutely no other words for the emotions that are coursing through my body. my face showed such emotion during that meeting but i don't care, i did not care. i was gypped my presidency last year far too many times. i'm elated it didn't happen again.

been real bad about this posting thing. life kinda sucks with being busy and all. gotta grow up in a few hundred days. who woulda thunk? i was supposed to have done this already, should've graduated in may of 2004 but didn't. 

i'm glad and not glad i stayed. it's helped but i feel that in a way i was only putting off the inevitable. but at the same time i need the time off. it was necessary to get my bearings, to realize what it is that i kind of wanted to do with my life. i mean i know that i want to work with helping people, children especially (and no no that in that nasty way) but after camp and hi-hello (the daycare center i worked at for two summers), i'm pretty sure that my life is aimed at helping. it sucks because it doesn't pay, but it's want i want to do. what will fulfill me, not my bank account or a lavish lifestyle but, it's what i want to do. especially at least for now. it's not that my mind will change about helping people, but at one point maybe helping will be in a different way. i can't do a 9 to 5 job in a cubicle or something that doesn't have me doing something. yes it's stressful and nerve-wrecking but that's how i love my life. i'm applying to the city year program (run my americorps). my dream was to do the peace corps but that's too much of a commitment, don't get me wrong i could. but i have too many things keeping me to the continental united states. mainly? my little sister. she is my life. i don't think people realize how much i truly mean that. it's scary but one of my biggest fears is my parents dying and my having to give up everything, not that i won't be able to, but what will i have? how will i be able to care for her? i mean i have cared for her but money wise, that's where my parents come in. so yeah i'm afraid of that. lets say i'm off doing some volunteer work, or low paying job and something happens... what do i do then? how would i be able to care for her then? and this is my irrational fear of something happening.

and now terri has been tickling me during this whole post, or at least 3/4 of the post. and now she's special and gets to be in this. lexie too, she asked me if i was writing a book. 

schools been interesting. it's fun having a lot of classes, lol... NOT. but they are interesting i will give you that. ohhhh and work has been great too. went to make my second payment plan payment (first one was $370 and change back in december) and i accidentally charged my parents the $1309.06 i owe. not just the $327.40... the full fuckin' 1300 dollars. so mad at myself. i mean it went through so yay! but still... i called them because checks didn't come in as i was expecting and well i know they are there for me and ... yeah. so now i owe my dad 1300 grand over the school. he said to take my time, which i will and won't. i want to graduate with the least, least amount of debt and the most amount of savings. i will probably go back to camp and save up those 1700 (after taxes). ohhh taxes coming back to me, going to the parents. woot! (yes i realized that right now as i was typing this)

okay back to buffy. it's the graduation part 2 episode and my favorite part is coming up so i'm off... that's a semi update... woot!

last night was a very interesting night... to say the absolute least.

i spent about 8 hours away from everything yesterday and it was a great 8 hrs. not that i don't love everyone an everything but i just needed ro-k time. then went to oscars with lex, jordie, and terri. terri was not aware of what had transpired in the last few days, so she was filled in. long story short, NOT happy but i had also calmed down with my last time, i really hope, in telling the story. then jordie gave me a pretty blue old navy sweater, which we are going to match (green for her though) for our RHSA secret snowflake thinger. 

came back to scuds with terri and lexie. then lexie gave me a present as well. i got a pretty blue aero sweater, which i'm wearing to today's Welcome Center secret snowflake thing. woot for gifts! terri did our hair (straighten) and make-up. yeah i got makeup put on me, i don't like wearing it bc i think i look uglier with makeup on. but i digress. then i got dressed up and then i changed my whole outfit lol. i ended up with my boobies out in a black halter, which terri and jordie told me i wasn't allowed to change. (wore a jacket and scarf and i left my scarf at 'cuddys :() some of the lenape crew was there (beryl, tracey, and colleen) it was awkard but walked away from it okay. terri talked to tracey and then next thing i know tracey is buying me a shot (red headed slut) and somehow we have made up. not perfect of course lol but we both realized we were both quite stupid with the things we did. i was stupid for picking a boy over her (or at least def not making time for her) and she shouldn't have reacted the way she did over a boy. but we are okay (:shrug:), not besties but talking again. beryl and colleen were nice too but meh... those friendships i don't know if i really would like back, if at all. beryl was funny though, outside drunk and smoking cigarettes and talking to random ass strangers. i couldn't take the cold and how she was embarrassing herself so i just left. had a red-headed slut shot with jordie (yay i buy my daughter a drink) and had overall i think about 4 or 5 amarettos sours last night. and my last drink of the night was a shot i brought for tracey and me, which this time was documented by terri. overall great night. had fun drinking and dancing. 

lexie and i got to talking this morning though and she brought up the point... well i'll finish soon kristyn is doing me a huge favor so i'll be back soon!

so i finally broke up with him. and for my first 6 hrs i think i've done a good job. i LOVE lexie (for reasoning with me), jordie (for walking over past midnight), tara (for being so calm and just smiling and wishing me the best), and especially kristyn (i only say this bc she's made me laugh the most-- and kris lol). thank you girls, from the bottom of my heart. i know you won't all see this but know i can't express to you guys how much i appreciate it. 

hard times are ahead, two and a half years almost, of an up and down relationship down the drain over cheating. (which i just realized that the saturday it happened, that sunday was our anniversary...) :sigh: i should have known but i wanted to hope and wish for better. but i will get over this. it will get better. and honestly i will find someone who is worth it. who will know what i'm worth and won't throw me around. 

but still it's 2 years with my first love and that will be hard. jordie is right when she says that i won't stop loving him, probably ever, but it is for the best. i can't change him. i can't have hope and faith in someone who doesn't want to try or make an effort. i'm too good of a person for having stayed for all that i did.

well now moving on. it'll be hard. but i went to dubs today while he was there, yes only the main door bc lex and i forgot milk, but still...

i got this. and even if every night i cry. i won't during the daytime.

Bitter Cold

 hopelessness and despair kicking in.
i'm curling up in my bed and crying until i'm dried out.

and then a new day will kick in. and i'll do it all over again.

and the nights will always be consumed with my despair.
and the days will always be consumed with my facade.

but the nights will creep up on me. and they will envelop me.
they will take over, from the moment it turns colder and colder.

that's how i'll become.

i will be awoken to the morning sun. the air outside will still be cold,
but like me
          it will thaw out and become warmer and nicer.

i will be in good company. they can't know what i'm going through though.
[they can't ever know again]                                    [this is my own fight]
to them i am happy (okay) with life and everything.

day by day. night by night.
smile by smile and tear by tear.

what will become of me? (who will i become?)
does anyone know? (does anyone want to know?)

who can save me? (who will care enough to?)
who knows? (not i, not anyone)

why will no one be there? (why is there no one left?)
because they can't know / won't know / don't want to know (they are done)

when will it be resolved? (when will it get better?)
or will it continue? (never, until it stops)

how will it end? (or will it start?)
better than it began. (back to it to begin anew)

why? (why not?)
pain and an emptiness that can't be fixed. (i can't let anyone in enough to trust them after all of this)


~ 159 days to go
